gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 128, Raptors 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Raptors, 128-111. D’Angelo Russell led the way for the Lakers with 25 points (7-14 3PT FG) and seven assists, while LeBron James (23 points, four rebounds, nine assists) and Anthony Davis (21 points, 12 rebounds) added a combined 44 points in the victory. RJ Barrett led all scorers with 28 points, along with six rebounds and six assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Lakers have won back-to-back games as they improve to 43-33 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 23-52.
